Package: HatchedPolygons
Type: Package
Title: Create a hatched area for SpatialPolygons
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(person("Sébastien", "Rochette", email = "sebastienrochettefr@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre")))
Maintainer: Sébastien Rochette <sebastienrochettefr@gmail.com>
Description: This package allows to create a area filled by SpatialLines to allow for hatched areas in SpatialPolygons.
    This may be particularly useful when SpatialPolygons show holes but also for drawing hatched areas in leaflet Polygons.
Depends: R (>= 3.2.0)
License: GPL
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports:
    dplyr,
    graphics,
    methods,
    sp,
    rgeos
Suggests:
    broom,
    plyr,
    leaflet,
    raster,
    ggplot2,
    tidyr,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
VignetteBuilder: knitr
